{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10807", "repo": "rails", "body": "@josevalim I've given up this approach \u2013 I don't think it'll be possible to continue down this road unless we make a major change to the template API. Specifically, it would be very difficult to keep supporting to ability to communicate between templates using instance variables. I find this to be a bad practice, but I bet people use it.\r\n\r\nIf this design is something that the core wants to move towards, we should consider how to rearchitect ActionView.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dba6bd3543c1510088ab"}, "issue_id": 10807, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21037607", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10807#issuecomment-21037607", "updated_at": "2013-07-16T12:07:06Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch", "login": "dasch", "gravatar_id": "a9cc05e6a7866e5fa9a7d107b5070174", "html_url": "https://github.com/dasch", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/a9cc05e6a7866e5fa9a7d107b5070174?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc6862d63b17d713ee14f3a405d9fde77.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 6351, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dasch/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-07-16T12:07:06Z", "id": 21037607, "owner": "rails"}
